        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Can I use single-wall corrugated sheets for hydroponics?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Single-wall may sag under water system weight. Double-wall is safer for most hydroponics setups. Triple-wall ensures maximum durability for larger systems or commercial-scale gardening.</p>
